240
00:17:56,205 --> 00:17:58,708
(7:28) إِنَّ اللهَ‌ لا يَأْمُرُ بِالْفَحْشاءِ

241
00:17:58,708 --> 00:17:59,721
This is a rule.

242
00:17:59,721 --> 00:18:02,404
And God's mercy

243
00:18:02,404 --> 00:18:10,000
will... with this... with knowing this about God's Mercy, do you think He will tell somebody "go kill your son, your only son"?

244
00:18:13,810 --> 00:18:16,559
You know, I expected many of us

245
00:18:16,559 --> 00:18:19,559
to go to Dr. Mansour, for example, and say

246
00:18:19,559 --> 00:18:28,068
we studied, we did research, we looked in the Quran and we discovered that God NEVER told Ibrahim to kill his son.

247
00:18:28,068 --> 00:18:31,950
You must stand up for your friend. God wants solid friends

248
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:39,527
who will not take any statement that contradicts God's qualities.

249
00:18:41,015 --> 00:18:43,998
If somebody accuses you of being a cheat

250
00:18:43,998 --> 00:18:48,991
and you are in a position of power, you are forming a cabinet, for example, a government

251
00:18:48,991 --> 00:18:52,184
and you are a president of some company, chairman of the board or something

252
00:18:52,184 --> 00:18:55,953
and you know that this person, even though he or she loves you,

253
00:18:55,953 --> 00:18:58,773
thinks wrongly that you are a cheat.

254
00:18:58,773 --> 00:19:03,798
How will you act towards this person?

255
00:19:03,798 --> 00:19:08,955
If you think of God that He commanded somebody to kill his son

256
00:19:08,955 --> 00:19:15,530
an act of vicious, merciless, a command,

257
00:19:15,530 --> 00:19:18,910
How will He feel about you on the Day of Judgement, if you feel that way?

258
00:19:18,910 --> 00:19:21,522
I discussed this matter with Dr. Mansour

259
00:19:21,522 --> 00:19:23,097
and we looked in the Quran and he said:

260
00:19:23,097 --> 00:19:24,934
"that's right." He read the verses.

261
00:19:24,934 --> 00:19:26,481
and it said

262
00:19:26,481 --> 00:19:28,114
(37:102) إِنِّىٓ أَرَىٰ فِى ٱلْمَنَامِ أَنِّىٓ أَذْبَحُكَ

263
00:19:28,114 --> 00:19:30,162
I see in a
dream that I am slaughtering you.

264
00:19:30,162 --> 00:19:32,015
And he said "that's right."

265
00:19:32,015 --> 00:19:34,166
God didn't order Ibrahim to kill his son.

266
00:19:34,166 --> 00:19:36,850
It doesn't say that in the Quran anywhere.

267
00:19:36,850 --> 00:19:41,121
(37:105) يَـٰٓإِبْرَٰهِيمُ (37:104) قَدْ صَدَّقْتَ ٱلرُّءْيَآ

268
00:19:41,121 --> 00:19:43,094
You believed your dream.

269
00:19:43,094 --> 00:19:44,190
if you look at it,

270
00:19:44,190 --> 00:19:47,618
but you see what they put in our heads as we were growing up, all of us

271
00:19:47,618 --> 00:19:50,783
and it comes from some distortions in the Bible

272
00:19:50,783 --> 00:19:53,742
that God ordered Ibrahim to "take your son and kill him."

273
00:19:53,742 --> 00:19:56,405
And it affected all of us

274
00:19:56,405 --> 00:19:58,202
but we have to look in the Quran

275
00:19:58,202 --> 00:20:01,248
and derive our information from the Quran.

276
00:20:01,248 --> 00:20:04,714
And had God ordered Ibrahim to kill his son,

277
00:20:04,714 --> 00:20:06,963
He will tell us

278
00:20:06,963 --> 00:20:08,224
but He wouldn't

279
00:20:08,224 --> 00:20:13,564
because God put the rule. He said He does not command فحشا , vice,

280
00:20:13,564 --> 00:20:16,330
gross matters.

281
00:20:16,330 --> 00:20:18,728
God will not be afraid to tell us

282
00:20:18,728 --> 00:20:20,734
if He did do that.

283
00:20:20,734 --> 00:20:23,224
I will accept it if He did do that.

284
00:20:23,224 --> 00:20:27,291
But He didn't. God's Mercy is beyond our wildest dreams.

285
00:20:27,291 --> 00:20:32,344
Ibrahim thought that he received the command from God in that dream

286
00:20:32,344 --> 00:20:38,684
but you see the crime is magnified because they tell us that the dream of the prophet is truth

287
00:20:38,684 --> 00:20:41,020
which makes them not human.

288
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:45,737
I mean, it turns into idolization of the prophets.

289
00:20:45,737 --> 00:20:49,808
So, it's a gross crime from many many angles.

290
00:20:56,739 --> 00:20:59,799
There's a few other things that I need to say about this.

291
00:20:59,799 --> 00:21:01,520
Let me see if I remember.

292
00:21:22,930 --> 00:21:25,896
I know there's something that I'm forgetting to say.

293
00:21:28,291 --> 00:21:30,675
So, maybe, I'll remember it in the prayer.

294
00:21:34,921 --> 00:21:37,619
It has to do with Ibrahim thinking

295
00:21:37,619 --> 00:21:39,870
that he was killing his son.

296
00:21:42,882 --> 00:21:44,075
So he went ahead,

297
00:21:44,075 --> 00:21:45,610
God intervened.

298
00:21:46,626 --> 00:21:48,427
It's exactly the other way around.

299
00:21:48,427 --> 00:21:51,566
I mean, it's contrary to what most people believe.

300
00:21:51,566 --> 00:21:54,132
God only intervened to save Ismail,

301
00:21:54,132 --> 00:21:57,163
Ibrahim's son.

302
00:21:59,703 --> 00:22:04,990
So, not only He did not order Ibrahim to kill his son, He intervened to save the son

303
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:07,892
because Ibrahim was a sincere believer.

304
00:22:07,892 --> 00:22:08,978
He was in God's kingdom.

305
00:22:08,978 --> 00:22:10,747
And God will not not let him.

306
00:22:10,747 --> 00:22:14,655
God will not allow you to fall in sin.

307
00:22:14,655 --> 00:22:17,769
God will not allow you to do something wrong when you're in His kingdom.

308
00:22:17,769 --> 00:22:20,423
He will not allow you. He will not let you do it.

309
00:22:21,983 --> 00:22:24,229
And you made the pledge, you are in God's kingdom.